Description: Sherd probably from neck and shoulder of pottery oenochoe; reddish brown glaze on the outside with added white decoration, retrograde 'S' band above wavy line.
Curator's comments: From same vase as Cambridge, Fitzwilliam Museum GR.3.1894
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.948)
